metadata.name: Flower 1
metadata.description: The still life of flowers is a collection of 1500 randomly generated flowers inspired by the likes of Claude Monet, Henri Mattise, Gustav Klimt and other impressionists from the 20th century. Flowers were born in javascript and were generated using a custom script. the idea of combining computer art with the still art of the 20th century  was invented during one of my morning walks through the local park reminiscing of the impressionist style used by the greats. Flowers are instantly revealed refresh your metadata and patiently wait for it to load.
